if('pacman' %in% rownames(installed.packages()) == FALSE) {
  install.packages('pacman', repos = "http://cran.case.edu")
}
pacman::p_load(gdata, rjags, rnoaa, ecoforecastR, MCMCvis)
knitr::opts_chunk$set(cache = TRUE)

Get the data.

work1 = read.xls("Mariana_Crow_MARK.xlsx", sheet = 1)
nyears <- 2013 - 1998 + 1
M <- matrix(0, nrow = 100, ncol = nyears)
ytemp <- as.matrix(work1[, 3:18])
y <- ytemp[which(rowSums(ytemp)!=0),] 
nind <- dim(y)[1] + dim(M)[1]
data = list(y = rbind(y, M), nind = nind, nyears = nyears, time = seq(1:(nyears + 5)))

JAGS code for the jolly seber model.

JS = "

model {

# Priors and constraints
for (i in 1:nind) {
  for (t in 1:(nyears + 5 - 1)) {
    phi[i, t] <- mean.phi
  } #t
  for (t in 1:(nyears + 5)) {
    p[i, t] <- mean.p
  } #t
} #i

mean.phi ~ dunif(0, 1)
mean.p ~ dunif(0, 1) 
igamma ~ dunif(0, 1)
beta[1] ~ dnorm(0, .367)
beta[2] ~ dnorm(0, .367)

# Likelihood 

for (i in 1:nind) {

  # First time step

  # State process
  z[i, 1] ~ dbern(igamma)
  # Observation process 
  y[i, 1] ~ dbern(mu1[i])
  mu1[i] <- z[i, 1] * p[i, 1] 

  # Subsequent time steps

  for (t in 2:(nyears + 5)) {

    # State process
    q[i, t - 1] <- 1 - z[i, t - 1]
    logit(gamma[i, t]) <- beta[1] + beta[2] * time[t]
    mu2[i, t] <- phi[i, t - 1] * z[i, t - 1] + gamma[i, t] * prod(q[i, 1:(t - 1)])
    z[i, t] ~ dbern(mu2[i, t])

  } #t

  for (t in 2:nyears) {

    # Observation process
    mu3[i, t] <- z[i, t] * p[i, t]
    y[i, t] ~ dbern(mu3[i, t])

  } #t

} #i

for (t in 1:(nyears + 5)) {
  N[t] <- sum(z[1:nind, t])
} #t

}
"
rinits <- function() {
  z <- matrix(1, nrow = nind, ncol = (nyears + 5))
  mean.phi <- runif(1, .7, .8)
  mean.p <- runif(1, .5, .6)
  beta <- runif(2, -1, 1)
  return(list(z = z, mean.phi = mean.phi, mean.p = mean.p, beta = beta))
}
params <- c("mean.phi", "mean.p", "N", "beta", "igamma")
jm <- jags.model(file = textConnection(JS), data = data, inits = rinits(), n.chains = 3, n.adapt = 1000)
## Compiling model graph
##    Resolving undeclared variables
##    Allocating nodes
## Graph information:
##    Observed stochastic nodes: 3200
##    Unobserved stochastic nodes: 4205
##    Total graph size: 34533
## 
## Initializing model
update(jm, n.iter = 10000)
samples = coda.samples(jm, n.iter = 5000, variable.names = params, thin = 1)
MCMCvis::MCMCsummary(samples, params = c("mean.phi", "mean.p", "beta", "igamma"), n.eff = TRUE)
##                mean         sd       2.5%        50%      97.5% Rhat n.eff
## mean.phi  0.7451912 0.02718802  0.6902533  0.7456416  0.7962602 1.00  1758
## mean.p    0.5698238 0.03888971  0.4939821  0.5695594  0.6454444 1.00   986
## beta[1]  -5.3540820 0.44900632 -6.2596102 -5.3279183 -4.5083126 1.02   456
## beta[2]   0.2143857 0.03882765  0.1391434  0.2129106  0.2909799 1.02   466
## igamma    0.2639388 0.03699290  0.1951113  0.2624225  0.3409080 1.00  4178
MCMCvis::MCMCtrace(samples, params = c("mean.phi", "mean.p", "beta", "igamma"), pdf = F)

saveRDS(samples, file = "JSTimeTrendGammaPlusForecast.rda")
n <- apply(MCMCvis::MCMCchains(samples, params = "N"), 2, quantile, probs = c(.025, .5, .975))
years <- seq(1998, 2018)
plot(range(1998, 2018), range(0, 80), type = 'n', xlab = 'year', ylab = 'crows')
ecoforecastR::ciEnvelope(years[1:17], n[1, 1:17], n[3, 1:17], col = "lightBlue")
ecoforecastR::ciEnvelope(years[17:21], n[1, 17:21], n[3, 17:21], col = "lightgreen")
lines(years, n[2, ], lwd = 1, col = "blue", lty = 1, type = 'l')
points(years, n[2, ], pch = 16, cex = 1)
